Remove the close button overlay from notifications entirely.

The close button (×) overlaps with the time label in the top-right
corner of notifications. Since the button can also be triggered via
middle/right click, swipe gesture, or keyboard (Delete), the visual
close button is redundant and causes visual clutter.

This patch removes the widget from both the UI blueprint and the
Vala source: the overlay, the GtkChild reference, the hover
controller (EventControllerMotion), the click signal, and the
transition duration setup.

